Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
changeBBoxMasterFromR0(25.10)                    changeBBoxMasterFromR0(25.10)

Name
       changeBBoxMasterFromR0  -  Converts  the  orientation of the master in-
       stance blackboxes from R0 to the specified orientation

Syntax
       changeBBoxMasterFromR0

       [-help]

       <black_box_cell>

       {R90 R180 R270 MX MX90 MY MY90}

       <new_x_origin><new_y_origin>

       Converts the orientation of the master instance blackboxes from  R0  to
       the specified orientation.

Parameters
       <black_box_cell>
              Specifies the name of the balckbox cell.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each changeBBoxMasterFromRO parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man changeBBoxMasterFromRO

       <new_x_origin>
              Specifies the new origin x-coordinate.

              Data_type: float, required

       <new_y_origin >
              Specifies the new origin y-coordinate.

              Data_type: float, required

       {R90 R180 R270 MX MX90 MY MY90}
              Specifies the new orientation value of the cell.

              The orientation value can be R0, R90, R180, R270, MX, MX90,  MY,
              or MY90.

              Data_type: enum, required

Examples
              *

                The  following commands converts the orientation of the master
                blackboxes CORE_CELL120 to R90.

                changeBBoxMasterFromR0 CORE_CELL120 {R90}

